<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css">
  <title>Escape the UnderWorld - First Puzzle</title>
  <script>
    function checkAnswer() {
      var userInput = document.getElementById('answerInput').value.toLowerCase();
      var correctAnswer = 'cerberus';

      if (userInput === correctAnswer) {
        // Redirect to the next page if the answer is correct
        window.location.href = '/secondPuzzleIntro'; // Update this to the correct route
      } else {
        // Display alert if the answer is incorrect
        alert("Percy says, 'That's not the right answer. Try again, or we'll be stuck here forever.'");
      }
    }
  </script>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="content-box">
    <h1>The Escape of the Underworld</h1>
    <p>
      Engraved on the box is the following riddle:
    </p>
    <blockquote><em>
      "Within the river where Styx does flow,<br>
      A creature guards with eyes aglow.<br>
      Answer me this, oh heroes bold,<br>
      What creature guards the underworld's gold?"
      <br><br>
      Speak the answer, let knowledge flow,<br>
      And the box shall open, its contents show.<br>
      Drachmas gleaming, a treasure untold,<br>
      For the journey ahead, a fortune to hold.
      </em>
    </blockquote>
    <form>
      <label for="answerInput">Enter the answer in order to open the box:</label>
      <input type="text" id="answerInput" name="answerInput" required>
      <button type="button" onclick="checkAnswer()">Submit Answer</button>
    </form>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
